<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SPICER 15-1/2 INCH (394 MM) SOLO&#8482; CLUTCH - REMOVE -
        CLUTCH ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install four (4) 7/16 x 14 x 1 3/4 UNC, hex head bolts in the holes provided in the clutch
                cover and into the clutch pressure plate to overcome the internal spring load. Tighten them finger
                tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a spline alignment tool into the release bearing assembly and driven discs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two (2) mounting bolts from the top position and install two (2) guide studs to
                facilitate removal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the remaining mounting bolts in a crisscross pattern.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the loose bolts and carefully slide the clutch with alignment tool off the guide
                studs.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
